        <p class="eyebrow">Driveways Tipperary</p>
        <h2 class="section-title" id="intro-heading">Driveways That Last — Built the Right Way in Tipperary</h2>
        <p>A crumbling, potholed driveway isn't just an eyesore — it drags down the entire kerb appeal of your home and can cause real drainage headaches down the line. Whether you're dealing with an uneven tarmac surface that's been patched one too many times, a muddy gravel entrance that turns into a quagmire every winter, or you simply want to give your property a fresh, clean look, Tipperary Groundworks is the local team to call. We've been transforming driveways across County Tipperary for years — and we treat every job, big or small, with the same level of care and craft.</p>
        <p>What sets us apart is simple: we do the groundwork properly. Every lasting driveway starts well below the surface — with correctly prepared sub-base, sound drainage, and well-laid edging. Skip those steps and even the finest surface will fail within a few years. Our team handles excavation, ground preparation, drainage, kerbing, and the finished surface all under one roof. No subcontractors, no passing the buck, no surprise extras. Just straight-talking tradespeople who take pride in their work and keep you in the loop from start to finish.</p>
        <p>We cover all of County Tipperary — from Tipperary Town to Clonmel, Nenagh to Thurles and everywhere in between. Call us today for a completely free, no-obligation site visit and written quote.</p>
