  <section class="services-blocks" aria-labelledby="services-heading">
    <div class="services-blocks-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">What We Install</p>
      <h2 class="section-title" id="services-heading">Our Driveway Services in Tipperary</h2>

      <!-- Resin Bound -->
      <div class="service-block">
        <div class="service-block-img">
          <img src="/assets/images/driveways-resin.jpg" alt="Resin bound driveway installation in Tipperary" width="580" height="400" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="service-block-text">
          <h3 id="resin-driveways">Resin Bound Driveways</h3>
          <p>Resin bound driveways are the fastest-growing choice for homeowners across Tipperary — and it's easy to see why. A blend of natural aggregate stone and clear UV-stable resin is mixed and trowelled to a seamless, smooth finish that looks stunning and performs brilliantly. The surface is fully permeable, meaning rainwater drains through rather than pooling — making it compliant with SuDS planning requirements and a smart choice for properties prone to surface water issues.</p>
          <p>We source quality aggregates in a wide range of colours and blends, so you can match your home's character — from warm amber tones that complement traditional Irish stone to cool greys that suit modern builds. Resin bound is also low maintenance: no weeds pushing through, no loose stones pinging against the car, and no staining from oil or leaves.</p>
          <p>Properly installed on a sound sub-base, a resin bound driveway is one of the most durable and attractive investments you can make in your property's exterior. We carry out every installation ourselves — no third-party laying crews.</p>
          <a href="/contact/" class="link-more" aria-label="Get a quote for resin bound driveways in Tipperary">Get a Free Quote →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tarmac -->
      <div class="service-block reversed">
        <div class="service-block-img">
          <img src="/assets/images/driveways-tarmac.jpg" alt="Tarmac driveway laid in Clonmel, County Tipperary" width="580" height="400" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="service-block-text">
          <h3 id="tarmac-driveways">Tarmac Driveways</h3>
          <p>Tarmac remains one of the most popular and cost-effective driveway options in Ireland — and when it's laid correctly, it's also one of the most reliable. A properly constructed tarmac driveway starts with thorough excavation, a well-compacted hardcore sub-base, and carefully graded falls to direct water away from the property. Get that foundation right and the surface will serve you for many years with minimal upkeep.</p>
          <p>We use quality hot-rolled asphalt and compact it with the appropriate machinery to achieve a consistent, professional finish. Tarmac is particularly well suited to larger driveways where cost per square metre is a priority, or properties with heavier vehicle use. It can also be resurfaced rather than fully replaced when it does eventually show wear, making it a genuinely long-term investment.</p>
          <p>From new installations to resurfacing worn driveways across Tipperary, our tarmac crews are experienced, efficient, and tidy — we leave your site clean and your new driveway ready to use in short order.</p>
          <a href="/contact/" class="link-more" aria-label="Get a quote for tarmac driveways in Tipperary">Get a Free Quote →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Block Paving -->
      <div class="service-block">
        <div class="service-block-img">
          <img src="/assets/images/driveways-block-paving.jpg" alt="Block paving driveway installed in Cashel, Tipperary" width="580" height="400" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="service-block-text">
          <h3 id="block-paving">Block Paving Driveways</h3>
          <p>Block paving brings a level of character and kerb appeal that no other surface quite matches. Individual paving bricks or flags are laid in patterns — herringbone, basket weave, stretcher bond — to create a driveway that genuinely enhances your home's appearance. Because individual blocks can be lifted and replaced, it's also practical: if a utility needs access beneath, there's no need to break up and relay an entire surface.</p>
          <p>We work with a range of block types and colours — concrete blocks, natural stone setts, and clay pavers — and we'll advise on what suits your property style, budget, and ground conditions. Good edge restraints and correct jointing compound are critical to a long-lasting result, and these are details we never cut corners on.</p>
          <p>Block paving does require a little more preparation time than tarmac or resin, but the finished result is a driveway that genuinely adds value to your home — and that's a worthwhile investment for many Tipperary homeowners.</p>
          <a href="/contact/" class="link-more" aria-label="Get a quote for block paving driveways in Tipperary">Get a Free Quote →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Concrete -->
      <div class="service-block reversed">
        <div class="service-block-img">
          <img src="/assets/images/driveways-concrete.jpg" alt="Concrete driveway finished in Nenagh, Tipperary" width="580" height="400" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="service-block-text">
          <h3 id="concrete-driveways">Concrete Driveways</h3>
          <p>Concrete is the workhorse of driveway surfaces — rock solid, incredibly durable, and low maintenance once cured. It's an excellent choice for properties with heavy vehicle traffic, farm entrances, or anywhere you need maximum load-bearing capacity. Reinforced concrete driveways can also be finished in various ways — brushed, exposed aggregate, or patterned — to give a more decorative result if appearance is important.</p>
          <p>The key to a concrete driveway that doesn't crack, shift, or spall is correct mix design, proper sub-base preparation, correct reinforcement, and well-placed expansion joints. Our team has the experience to get all of these details right, ensuring your concrete driveway remains solid and crack-free for many years to come.</p>
          <p>We also handle all associated groundworks — excavation, levelling, drainage, and edging — as part of every concrete driveway installation across County Tipperary.</p>
          <a href="/contact/" class="link-more" aria-label="Get a quote for concrete driveways in Tipperary">Get a Free Quote →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Gravel & Decorative Stone -->
      <div class="service-block">
        <div class="service-block-img">
          <img src="/assets/images/driveways-gravel.jpg" alt="Gravel and decorative stone driveway in Thurles, Tipperary" width="580" height="400" loading="lazy">
        </div>
        <div class="service-block-text">
          <h3 id="gravel-driveways">Gravel & Decorative Stone Driveways</h3>
          <p>Gravel remains a popular, cost-effective, and visually appealing choice for driveways across rural and semi-rural Tipperary. A properly installed gravel driveway — with a sound compacted sub-base, a root-barrier membrane, solid edging restraints, and the right stone size and depth — is a practical, attractive, and long-lasting option. The key word is "properly": a gravel drive thrown down without correct preparation will spread, sink, and grow weeds within a season.</p>
          <p>We install gravel driveways with the same care as any other surface: correct excavation, membrane installation, compacted stone base, quality edging, and a generous layer of your chosen gravel or decorative stone — pea gravel, slate chippings, crushed limestone, golden granite, and more. The result is a driveway that looks well, drains freely, and stays in place.</p>
          <p>Gravel is also a brilliant option if you're on a tighter budget but still want a smart, well-finished entrance — and it can always be upgraded to resin bound at a later stage.</p>
          <a href="/contact/" class="link-more" aria-label="Get a quote for gravel driveways in Tipperary">Get a Free Quote →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
