    <div class="pricing-inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">Pricing Guidance</p>
      <h2 class="section-title" id="pricing-heading">What Does a New Driveway Cost in Tipperary?</h2>
      <div class="pricing-intro">
        <p>We know that cost is one of the first things on your mind — and we'll always be upfront about it. Driveway pricing in Ireland varies considerably depending on a number of factors, and any contractor who gives you a firm price without seeing the site is guessing. That said, here's an honest guide to what typically drives cost, and the general price landscape for different surface types.</p>
        <p>As a broad rule, gravel and tarmac tend to be the most accessible options per square metre, concrete and block paving sit in the mid-to-higher range, and resin bound driveways — while carrying a higher cost per square metre — often represent excellent long-term value given their longevity and minimal maintenance needs. Every quote we issue is fully itemised so you know exactly what you're paying for.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pricing-grid">
        <div class="price-card">
          <h3>Gravel Driveways</h3>
          <p>Generally the most affordable option. Cost rises with size, edging complexity, and stone type. Great value for rural entrances and larger properties where budget is a priority.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="price-card">
          <h3>Tarmac Driveways</h3>
          <p>Mid-range cost per square metre. Price is driven by total area, excavation depth required, drainage needs, and whether kerbing or edging is being installed. Very competitive for larger areas.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="price-card">
          <h3>Resin Bound Driveways</h3>
          <p>Higher cost per square metre than tarmac or gravel, reflecting the quality of materials and skill involved. Offset by extremely low maintenance costs and outstanding longevity. Highly popular in Tipperary right now.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="price-card">
          <h3>Block Paving</h3>
          <p>Costs vary with block type, pattern complexity, and edging requirements. Natural stone setts carry a premium over concrete blocks. The most labour-intensive option — and the most impactful on kerb appeal.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="price-card">
          <h3>Concrete Driveways</h3>
          <p>Mid-to-upper range depending on reinforcement, finish type, and drainage. Extremely durable and low maintenance once laid. Cost-effective over a long time horizon.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="price-card">
          <h3>Key Cost Factors</h3>
          <p>All driveway prices are affected by: total area (m²), existing surface removal, excavation depth, drainage work required, ground conditions, access for machinery, and your choice of edging or kerbing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="pricing-note">&#9888; We do not publish set prices online because every site is different. The only accurate price is one based on a proper site visit. Our quotes are free, no-obligation, and issued in writing — call <a href="tel:+353873566934" style="color:var(--pd-accent);font-weight:700;">+353 87 356 6934</a> or fill in the form below to book yours.</p>
