        <div class="faq-item" role="listitem">
          <button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-a3" id="faq-q3">
            Do I need planning permission for a new driveway in Ireland?
            <span class="faq-icon" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
            </span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-a3" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-q3">
            <p>In most cases, replacing or upgrading a driveway in front of a house does not require planning permission in Ireland, provided the surface is permeable or water is directed to a soakaway or drainage system on the property. SuDS-compliant surfaces like resin bound aggregate are especially well suited. If your property is in a protected structure or an Architectural Conservation Area, you should check with Tipperary County Council first. We're happy to advise.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

