          <div class="faq-answer" id="faq-a4" role="region" aria-labelledby="faq-q4">
            <p>Driveway costs vary considerably depending on size, surface type, access, existing ground conditions, and drainage requirements. Gravel is typically the most affordable option, tarmac and concrete sit in the mid-range, and resin bound or block paving tend to carry a higher price per square metre due to the skill and materials involved. The best way to get an accurate figure is to request your free no-obligation quote from us.</p>
